# Post-Sprint Deploy Workflow (MarketWall)

Run this workflow **automatically at the end of every sprint** unless the user explicitly opts out.

**Repo:** https://github.com/mrnguyenlk-byte/marketwall.git  
**Production:** https://btrading.org (Vercel project `marketwall`, branch `main`)

## Hard rules (never violate)

- Do **NOT** push if `npm run build` fails
- Do **NOT** force push (`--force`, `--force-with-lease`)
- Do **NOT** reset the database (`prisma migrate reset`, `db push --force-reset`, drop tables)
- Do **NOT** delete production data
- Do **NOT** commit `.env.local`, `.env`, credentials, or API keys
- Do **NOT** stage `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo` — unstage if accidentally added
- Only ask the user for **credentials, billing, or irreversible/dangerous actions**

## Step 1 — Determine sprint number

Read `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md` → **Sprint Progress**. Use the sprint number just completed (or the highest in-progress sprint being closed).

## Step 2 — Local build gate

```bash
npm run build
```

**If build fails:** fix errors locally, then re-run. Do **not** commit or push until build passes.

### Common fix: lockfile out of sync (Vercel/CI pattern)

If logs mention `pnpm-lock.yaml` / lockfile mismatch / frozen lockfile:

```bash
pnpm install
npm run build
```

Commit updated lockfile **only after** local build passes. Prefer `pnpm-lock.yaml` when Vercel uses pnpm; keep `package-lock.json` in sync if npm is the local package manager — do not leave conflicting lockfiles broken.

## Step 3 — Commit (build must pass first)

```bash
git status
git add .
```

Before committing, verify staged files:

- **Reject:** `.env.local`, `.env`, `*.pem`, credentials, `.next/`, `node_modules/`
- **Unstage:** `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo` (`git reset HEAD tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`)

```bash
git commit -m "Sprint X complete"
```

Replace `X` with the actual sprint number (e.g. `Sprint 5 complete`).

## Step 4 — Push

```bash
git push origin main
```

No force push. If push is rejected (non-fast-forward), pull/rebase normally — never force.

## Step 5 — Vercel deployment verification

After push, wait for Vercel to deploy `main`:

1. Record pushed SHA: `git rev-parse HEAD`
2. Poll deployment status (prefer CLI; fallback to GitHub/Vercel dashboard):
   - `npx vercel ls marketwall --prod` (requires Vercel auth)
   - or `gh api repos/mrnguyenlk-byte/marketwall/deployments` and match `main` SHA
3. Wait until status is **Ready** (poll ~30s, timeout ~15 min)
4. Confirm production serves the latest commit:
   - Deployment SHA matches `git rev-parse HEAD`
   - https://btrading.org loads without 5xx

**If Vercel deploy fails:** fetch build logs (`npx vercel inspect <deployment-url> --logs` or Vercel dashboard), fix the root cause, rebuild locally, commit fix, push again. Repeat until production is green.

## Step 6 — Sprint audit

Create `SPRINT_X_AUDIT.md` at repo root. Follow the established pattern (see `SPRINT5_DATA_REALTIME_AUDIT.md`):

```markdown
# Sprint X — <Title> Audit

**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Scope:** <one-line summary>
**Build:** `npm run build` ✅
**Deploy:** https://btrading.org — commit `<short-sha>` ✅

## Summary
<what shipped, key behavior changes>

## Files changed
| File | Change |
|------|--------|

## Verification
- [ ] Local build passed
- [ ] Pushed to `main`
- [ ] Vercel production Ready
- [ ] btrading.org serves latest commit
```

Update `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md` Sprint Progress table with a row linking the audit file.

## When to stop and ask the user

- Missing `TWELVE_DATA_API_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`, Vercel token, or GitHub push access
- Vercel billing / quota / team permission errors
- Any action that would reset DB, wipe prod data, or force-push

Otherwise: fix build/deploy issues autonomously and report results in the audit.
